# Introduction

This is my submission for the *Good Plot / Bad Plot* assignment.  

The dataset visualized here comes from the **TidyTuesday Outer Space Objects dataset** (2024-04-23). It contains every known launch of space objects (satellites, debris, etc.) by country and year.  

### Load Libraries and data


```{r}
#| message: false
#| warning: false

library(tidyverse)
library(rnaturalearth)
library(ggthemes)
library(mapdata)
library(gganimate)
library(viridis)
library(sf)

# Load data
space_objects <- readr::read_csv("https://raw.githubusercontent.com/rfordatascience/tidytuesday/main/data/2024/2024-04-23/outer_space_objects.csv")
world <- map_data("world")
```



# Bad Plot
*_Launchapalooza_* is intended to be be visually painful, confusing, and misleading by violating core principles of

### Data Prep


```{r}
#| message: false
#| warning: false
# Only had name of country so needed to match that to coordinates using rnaturalearth
countries <- rnaturalearth::ne_countries(scale = "medium", returnclass = "sf") %>%
  st_centroid() %>%
  mutate(lon = st_coordinates(.)[,1],
         lat = st_coordinates(.)[,2]) %>%
  st_drop_geometry() %>%
  select(iso_a3, lon, lat)

# Join coordinates so I can plot them as points
launches_coords <- space_objects %>%
  left_join(countries, by = c("Code" = "iso_a3")) %>%
  drop_na(lon, lat)
```


